Cargo Ship Is Partially Afloat, Raising Hopes of Restoring Trade Traffic

  • The Ever Given, the giant cargo ship blocking the Suez Canal, was partially refloated and close to fully freed early Monday.
  • Salvage teams, working on both land and water for five days and nights, were ultimately assisted by forces more powerful than machines: the moon and the tides.
  • The salvage operation was one of the largest in modern history, with the smooth functioning of global trading hanging in the balance.

It took 10 years to build the Suez Canal in the 1800s, and one day and one giant ship to clog it in 2021.
